      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Many Lessons of Whitewater</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stanley Birnbaum letter says that what happened to Pres Clinton in Paula Jones suit should never be permitted to happen again to an American president; calls for constitutional amendment reversing Supreme Court decision that allowed civil case to proceed during Clinton's term in office (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Whitewater Verdict'' (editorial, Sept. 21):</p>
        <p>It is time to put some portion of the Clinton brouhaha to some constructive purpose. What happened to Bill Clinton in the Paula Jones case should never be permitted to happen to an American president again. We need a constitutional amendment reversing the Supreme Court's decision that allowed Paula Jones's civil case to go forward during Mr. Clinton's term in office.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Whitewater Verdict'' (editorial, Sept. 21):</p>
        <p>It is time to put some portion of the Clinton brouhaha to some constructive purpose. What happened to Bill Clinton in the Paula Jones case should never be permitted to happen to an American president again. We need a constitutional amendment reversing the Supreme Court's decision that allowed Paula Jones's civil case to go forward during Mr. Clinton's term in office.</p>
        <p>The events that followed the court's decision demonstrate the need for such an amendment. The decision upsets the balance of power by giving the judiciary and the legal system far too much power over the executive branch, power that can be exploited politically, and was.</p>
        <p>Except in cases in which an emergency exists or some damage that cannot be remedied will be caused by  delay, civil actions against a sitting president should not be allowed to proceed.</p>
        <p>STANLEY BIRNBAUM  Santa Rosa, Calif., Sept. 21, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a lawyer.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
